"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-16T13:12:28.000Z","msg":"竟然快過錫菲聯同阿森納炒領隊<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},{"pid":"fbe2397b417ea5e297ea8c057b1e5de372b2df12","tid":2328241,"uid":312758,"like":6,"dislike":0,"score":6,"quote":{"pid":"d7374049b15e3e1dc12702a5bfdda42b10fd68a9","tid":2328241,"uid":111460,"like":1,"dislike":1,"score":0,"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-16T13:12:28.000Z","msg":"竟然快過錫菲聯同阿森納炒領隊<img src=\"/assets/faces/normal/sosad.gif\" class=\"hkgmoji\" />"},"citedBy":1,"replyTime":"2020-12-16T13:18:09.000Z","msg":"錫菲件老野有啲地位，應該仲有得兜<br />\n<br />\n但係阿黑奴件奶共達早就應該收皮"}],"pinned":{"pid":"3947e5b14821434455c712ea643c894e68b756ce","tid":2328241,"uid":170821,"like":2,"dislike":0,"score":2,"citedBy":0,"replyTime":"2020-12-16T17:12:27.000Z","msg":"<strong><span class=\"x-large\">ALBION APPOINT SAM ALLARDYCE</span><br />\n<br />\n<img src=\"https://cdn.wba.co.uk/sites/default/files/styles/cc_2000x1500/public/2020-12/Welcome%20Sam%204x3.jpg\" data-thumbnail-src=\"https://i.lih.kg/thumbnail?u=https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.wba.co.uk%2Fsites%2Fdefault%2Ffiles%2Fstyles%2Fcc_2000x1500%2Fpublic%2F2020-12%2FWelcome%2520Sam%25204x3.jpg&h=5f57c844&s={SIZE}\" /><br />\n<br />\nWest Bromwich Albion are delighted to confirm the appointment of Sam Allardyce as the club&rsquo;s new Head Coach.</strong><br />\n<br />\nThe experienced boss, who has 512 Premier League games to his name, arrives at Albion with his long-time assistant, Sammy Lee. <br />\n<br />\nThe Dudley-born manager returns to The Hawthorns more than 30 years after starting his coaching career with the Baggies under former boss Brian Talbot in 1989.   <br />\n<br />\nHe has now taken the reins at a record eight Premier League clubs, including Bolton Wanderers, West Ham United, Sunderland, Crystal Palace and in his last role, Everton.<br />\n<br />\nThe 66-year-old, who agreed terms on an 18-month contract earlier today, will take training on Thursday in preparation for Sunday&rsquo;s Premier League fixture against Aston Villa (ko 7.15pm). <br />\n<br />\nSporting and Technical Director, Luke Dowling, said: &ldquo;In Sam we have a man who has a proven Premier League pedigree with a track record of improving every club he has managed. <br />\n<br />\n&ldquo;We believe and, more importantly, Sam believes we have a group of players that have the quality needed to give the club its best chance of Premier League survival.&rdquo;<br />\n<br />\n<a href=\"https://www.wba.co.uk/news/albion-appoint-sam-allardyce\" data-sr-url=\"https://r.lihkg.com/link?u=https%3A%2F%2Fwww.wba.co.uk%2Fnews%2Falbion-appoint-sam-allardyce&d=c%2B6PkbrQ5MzYtHY5m9tE12hNlLB%2BLbsdBqu6cuXqlDc%3D&h=204699da\" target=\"_blank\">https://www.wba.co.uk/news/albion-appoint-sam-allardyce</a>"}}